	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Absor discussion threads postponed.</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=353536" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abm.asp?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    The Baltimore Fan Faire is blasting off this weekend and Absor is taking a trip to join in the festivities. <a href=http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/053886.html target=_blank>Here</a> he writes about future discussions.<blockquote><p><b>I probably will have limited access to the Internet while I'm out of town. So I won't be posting much, if at all. And I won't be doing too much reading of the class threads either, sorry.</p><p>When I get back I'll be starting three threads (I think I'll be back on Monday…), Rogue, Paladin and Ranger Talk. I'm moving Rangers up because I want them all done by the end of the week. I will also be starting Necromancer and Magician talk threads later in the week. Some time the week after I'll be posting my lists for each class.</p><p>I wanted to, once again, stress that the whole idea with all of this is to balance the classes, or get as close as we can. This might very well mean an increase in the strength of a class. But it might also mean a reduction in the strength of a class. We will consider 'nerfs' if they seem necessary. I am not suggesting that we are looking to nerf anything, but I also want you to be aware that we may do so.</p><p>So I'll see who I see in Baltimore. Have a good weekend.</p><p>Alan</b></p></blockquote>

Also meet our own Xanthus there this weekend, and stop him and say hi!
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
