			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Absor, there are quite a few problems to deal with when it comes to the classes.  I do not feel like you are giving yourself and VI enough time to examine the classes properly and come up with positive solutions that will improve the game.  More than a week is needed.  <BR>
<BR>
As a frustrated wizard, of course I want attention directed to that class, but I also feel that there are several other classes that have legitimate concerns that are just as important as the ones posted on the wizard boards (I think it's to the 6th thread now?).<BR>
<BR>
We are players AND customers.  Please do not belittle our concerns by not giving them time and consideration.  After reading some of the other boards (other than the Wizard) there are quite a few intelligent people that have suggested real solutions.  Sure, you have to weed through the crap put out by some.  Sadly, you can't escape that.  <BR>
<BR>
This is not a flame.  I realize your job is frustrating and without much appreciation.  But, it might help everyone to get a better idea how to approach you with our concerns if we knew what your job description is.  Is your role more of a player advocate to VI?  A point person for communicating with VI?  Or does VI consider you just to be the voice on their behalf?<BR>
<BR>
The reason I ask this is after skimming the boards, I see we (players) seem to have no one on our side besides other players.  It's like we have been thrust into the role of an adversary against VI.  I can't speak for everyone, but I don't like that at all.  Down the road, the results would be unfavorable on both sides (we lose the enjoyment of what could be a fantastic game and you lose customers).<BR>
<BR>
Please work to improve your relationship with us, the customers.  Otherwise, the moment someone shows up with an enjoyable alternative the players will disappear (I don't consider Asheron's Call as one, or Ultima Online either).<BR>
<BR>
Thank you for your time and effort.<BR>
<BR>
Macksin Shadizarr<BR>
31st Level Wizard<BR>
Merciless Justice (officer-casters)<BR>
Veeshan Server<BR>
<BR>
&quot;If it makes you feel better to call it evil before you slay it, so be it.  I have no such illusions.  I am here simply to blow stuff up.&quot;<BR>

