			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				No offense taken. <BR>
<BR>
I have 8 characters on BB and to me adventuring, exploring and having fun is more important than power leveling. Playing a character that is not balanced could actually be an interesting challenge.<BR>
<BR>
I have read the various posts with all their ingenious ideas on how to make a class more powerful but NONE I have seen argue convincingly that any class is underpowered or offer any data or way to measure balance.<BR>
<BR>
One important point I have seen mentioned is how certain classes either are always welcomed or rarely welcomed in high level groups.  To me, that's a more important issue than balance.<BR>
<BR>
Another aspect of that data I mentioned is class distribution. If, say 25% of the people at levels one through 20 are rangers but only 15% at levels 50% plus are then either:<BR>
<BR>
1) Rangers are no fun to play post 50 and people won't play them.<BR>
<BR>
2) It is too difficult to level them and people wont play them.<BR>
<BR>
This would suggest but not prove that  rangers are underpowered at higher levels.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
