	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Joe ..<BR>
<BR>
Forgive me but I  must wholehaertedly  disagree with  your  days played as to level analysis.<BR>
<BR>
Please let me explain:<BR>
<BR>
#1  more intricate classes ( Ie: not the power and glory  classes)  are normally  played by  the more in-depth gamer familiar with gaming and looking for more then the  typical power leveling experience.  Hence, they are  doing skills exploring, and meeting new  people  rather  then  gaming.  This does not make them underpowered.  <BR>
<BR>
#2.  However,  just  b\c  ( and  please no power and glory  class  take offense)  the power classes are at a higher level faster does not mean they are  overpowered. <BR>
<BR>
#3.  Also,  let us  look at warriors if a warrior wishes to excell  alone then his advancement will be slower then one who  chooses to  go throuh life as part of a  group.  ( ie:  he  must  sit to heal request bufs etc.)  But when they are  both  50  they will have the same skills, and abilities.  Granted  everyone will be a little  diff  but the standard level 50 skills are  avaliable to both.<BR>
<BR>
So,  hence  I feel  that  considering everything,  skills, guilds , exploring,  item hunting ( I want thsoe azure sleeves! ) going strictly by the  days played as to level comparison  could be  misleading at  best.  <BR>
<BR>
Not a  flame  Joe  just  friendly  conversation and my opinion. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
    
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
