	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There are only a few ways of determining whether classes are &quot;overpowered&quot; or &quot;underpowered.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Verant has an enormous database of player info - - - levels, classes and races and how many days days played. They could generate very nice graphs or charts showing a population distribution.<BR>
<BR>
Say for example that a certain class at level 50 had a much longer days played than another class. That would certainly suggest that class was underpowered.<BR>
<BR>
So much of these discussions have been about ideas to make one class more power but almost none have realy proved that a certain class needs to be improved.<BR>
<BR>
If a class seems to be underpowered based on that objective data, Verant could also look at ways they could be made more useful to groups. Assume. for the sake of argument that wizards were overpowered, maybe they could have their mana caps raised. The increased firepower would make them more useful during battle to the rest of their party. Being more desirable to a group could increase their opportunities to gain exp.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
